Failure scenario: when `sample_time_utc` retained ISO `+00:00` suffix, ClickHouse `DateTime64(3, 'UTC')` parser rejects the row (`Cannot parse input: expected '"' before '+00:00'`).
Verification: prior to normalization, static reproduction using `_clickhouse_datetime` returned `2026-03-19T12:34:56.123456+00:00`, which matched the production crash log.
